                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Assignment of mortgage.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116047">Roche Court (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1664">16 Chas. II. Aug. 1, 1664</origDate>. Indenture quadripartite made between (1) Simon Bennet of Beachampton,
                        Buckinghamshire, esq., (2) Thomas Russell of the Inner Temple, London,
                        gent., (3) George Savile of Bakewell, Derbyshire, gent., and Thomas Gregge,
                        citizen and Pewterer of Lond, and (4) William Savile of Bakewell,
                        Derbyshire, gent., reciting the deeds of Oliver Brocas and Richard Brocas of
                        6 August 1656 and 27 January 1657, being an assignment of mortgage from (1)
                        to (3) of the manor of North Farham otherwise Roch Court, Hampshire, with
                        the manor house and lands in North Farham; with a receipt attached, dated 1
                        August 1664 of monies from George Savile and Thomas Gregge, signed by Simon
                        Bennet) (signed and sealed by Simon Bennet and Thomas Russell).</p>
